\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 To ensure our findings would represent real life behavior in the everyday settings in which they are of interest, we chose to conduct a free-living study to test our device. In a free-living study, participants go about their normal daily routines while wearing test devices. To ensure our algorithms generalized across individuals, all members of our research team, three male and one female students at Northwestern University, volunteered for our free-living study. Our ages ranged between (20-25) and all of a healthy weight. After being trained by our instructors on how to use the devices, we went about our everyday lives, collecting data on as many meals or snacks as possible. We permitted ourselves to turn off the sensor suite for situations where continuous monitoring might be cumbersome, inappropriate, or personal.
